[Download RAW <a href="?l=namedroppers&m=95837784627048&q=mbox">message</a> or <a href="?l=namedroppers&m=95837784627048&q=raw">body</a>]</b>

This incident (finger looping and repeating the same request ad nauseam)
appears to justify one of Paul Mockapetris remarks about the tuning of
name servers, i.e. that we need both "positive caching" but also
"negative cacheing". With negative cacheing, a name server will remember
that a request for some &lt;name,info,domain&gt; was issued previously and
failed, and will immediately report the failure to its client without
polluting the net.

Will this negative cacheing policy be implemented in the next release of
"bind"?

Christian Huitema

